{
  "doc_id": "33880",
  "text": "For epoxy/graphene nanocomposites, graphene can significantly improve the physical and chemical properties of the matrix at extremely low loadings [CITATION_1] , and this enhancement could only be achieved when graphene is homogeneously dispersed in the matrix. The uniformly-dispersed graphene could share external stress to avoid stress concentration and impede crack propagation, which leads to the improvements in the mechanical properties. On the contrary, poorly-dispersed graphene acts as stress raiser and causes stress concentration, resulting in the deterioration of the mechanical properties [CITATION_2] .",
